# ============================================================
# Amuche's Oven — Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env for local dev with Netlify CLI
# Set these same values in Netlify Dashboard → Site → Environment variables
# NEVER commit real values to git
# ============================================================

# Supabase — get these from your Supabase project dashboard
# Settings → API → Project URL & anon public key
SUPABASE_URL=''
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=''

# ── HOW TO SET UP ──────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. Create a Supabase project at https://supabase.com
# 2. Copy your Project URL and anon key from Settings > API
# 3. Paste them above (for local dev)
# 4. In Netlify Dashboard: Site > Environment Variables > Add
#    - SUPABASE_URL = your project URL
#    - SUPABASE_ANON_KEY = your anon key
# 5. Run SQL files in order in Supabase SQL Editor:
#    sql/01_schema.sql → sql/02_rls.sql → sql/03_storage.sql → sql/04_seed.sql
# 6. Create admin user in Supabase: Authentication > Users > Invite
#
# ── LOCAL DEVELOPMENT ─────────────────────────────────────
# Install Netlify CLI: npm install -g netlify-cli
# Link your site:     netlify link
# Start dev server:   netlify dev
# This auto-injects env vars and runs inject-env.js
